snippet.textDisplay: Ok this is just bizarre. This was the most normal interview I have ever seen Will Ferrell give. The irony being it is usually a wacky interview for others. So it's some kind of upside down world where the funny guy gives a normal interview and other people hack and cough and wheeze and die? I am not saying there was anything wrong with the interview (This show only works because Sean Evans is a great interviewer) just awkward to see Will Ferrell be himself instead of some kind of character. I think he was genuinely terrified of the spicy wings. I would not want to do this interview ever. i can't handle spicy food and I don't understand why Da Bomb is still there. Everyone says it is terrible and you are actually trying to sell your own hot sauce right? So make them eat garbage? There have to be 10 hot sauces that don't taste like shit in the world. From my friends who have tried the hotsauces you advertise her most of them are good and Da Bomb tastes terrible.

snippet.textDisplay: Ya ok I wasn't aware of the warring fandoms whatsoever. I like both shows I truly enjoy friends. But it doesn't hold a candle to seinfeld it just doesn't. The writing the jokes the scenarios encountered. The "camaraderie of the friends is what makes friends Friends. But it isn't a better show by any metric. It is attractive people going through their everyday hijinks in unrealistically large apartments. Both have very little minority representation as well. Seinfeld is better written period. There isn't a contest here. Both shows are great for very different reasons but one is better. Friends is more about Nostalgia. Seinfeld will always be funny.
